Reasoning: 
1. cs.AI - The paper proposes a deep Q-learning approach to optimize the dispatching of vehicles and drones for same-day delivery. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence. 
2. cs.LG - The paper uses deep learning techniques to learn the value of assigning customers to either drones or vehicles. This falls under the category of machine learning. 
3. cs.RO - The paper deals with the optimization of dispatching vehicles and drones for same-day delivery, which falls under the category of robotics. 
4. cs.SY - The paper deals with the coordination of a heterogeneous fleet of vehicles and drones, which falls under the category of control systems. 
5. cs.MA - The paper deals with the coordination of multiple agents (vehicles and drones) to achieve a common goal, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems.
